Trisha Campbell is an Assistant Professor of Writing and Rhetoric with a designated emphasis on Digital Rhetoric and Theory. Her work on the murder networks is finding audiences at national conferences and internationally peer-reviewed journals. Her work discusses an array of issues on race, human and non human agents, network logic, and new materialist rhetoric with regard to violence, digital publics, and our radically connected inhabitancy of the world. To this end, she teaches, makes, and composes projects--digital and textual, creative and critical--that imagine work in the humanities to be hinged on an interceding praxis. She is currently revising her manuscript, <em>Murder Networks.</em>_x000D__x000D_
